<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - INSTALL - SHIMMING PROCEDURE FOR TAPERED BEARINGS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1301705" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="6">
        <title>SHIMMING PROCEDURE FOR TAPERED BEARINGS</title>
        <para>The shimming procedure can be done in the horizontal or vertical position. The procedure is done the
            same.
        </para>
        <para>Shims must be aligned properly or else the rear bearing cover may be damaged when final torque is
            applied.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the countershaft straps. Make sure a 0.125 countershaft rear bearing shim is
                installed (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017o0">Figure 240</hotlnk>). Be sure the countershaft rear bearing races are seated
                in the bearing bores.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017o0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017o0" filename="../figg13/G13017O0.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 240. Countershaft Rear Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two (2) new 3/8" x 1" bolts without washers directly across from each other in each
                bearing cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017o1">Figure 241</hotlnk>). Tapped holes in auxiliary case must be free of thread
                adhesive.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017o1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017o1" filename="../figg13/G13017O1.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 241. Bolts In Bearing Cover</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten the bolts to 7 in-lbs. (.8 N&#8226;m) of torque (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017o2">Figure 242</hotlnk>).
                <emph type="bold">Do not install the countershaft rear bearing cover gasket.</emph>
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017o2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017o2" filename="../figg13/G13017O2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 242. Tighten Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the output shaft six (6) times clockwise, then six (6) times counterclockwise to seat
                the countershaft rear bearings. Use a feeler gauge, as close to each bolt location as possible, and
                measure the gap between the countershaft rear bearing cover and the auxiliary case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017o3">Figure 243</hotlnk>). Record the measurements. Using the average measurement,
                refer to the shimming chart to identify the proper shim.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017o3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017o3" filename="../figg13/G13017O3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 243. Measure Gap</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the countershaft rear bearing cover and gauging shim.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the selected shim on the rear countershaft bearing race (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017o4">Figure 244</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017o4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017o4" filename="../figg13/G13017O4.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 244. New Gasket On Countershaft Rear Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a new gasket on countershaft rear bearing cover mounting surface (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017o4">Figure 244</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the countershaft rear bearing cover over the new gasket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017o5">Figure 245</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017o5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017o5" filename="../figg13/G13017O5.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 245. Countershaft Rear Bearing Cover Over Gasket</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Eaton/Fuller Sealant #71205 or Loctite 242 to the retaining bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the retaining bolts, and tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#8226;m) of
                torque.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Repeat Steps 1-8 for the other countershaft rear bearing cover.</para>
        </step1>
